        ]
      ],
      "content": "Day 10,847. The signal came again at 03:00. Same coordinates. Same sequence.\n\nI went out to the bearing. I took the boat. I know what I found.\n\nI won't write it here. If you've read this far, you already know. You lit the lamp. You heard the signal. You decoded the coordinates.\n\nYou'll go too.\n\nI understand now why the keepers before me never left. Why they stayed for decades. Why the logbooks all end the same way \u2014 mid-sentence, mid-thought, as if they simply stopped needing to write.\n\nThe light should stay dark. But it won't. Someone always lights it.\n\n*\u2014 H.M., Keeper*"
